JUDICIAL BIOGRAPHICAL INFORMATION
This listing presents the appointment and assignment history of each judge currently serving in the New Jersey Judiciary. The information is
presented by judge in alphabetical order and includes current assignment, initial oath date, all assignments since appointment, law school
graduated from, whether the judge has tenure, reappointment date, and year of mandatory retirement. This information will be updated
monthly.
CLICK HERE FOR JUDGE SEARCH OR SCROLL THROUGH DOCUMENT
Key to Fields:
Court - The court to which the judge was appointed (Superior Court, Tax Court, or Supreme Court)
Mandatory retirement - Year at which judge will turn seventy (70) years of age
Tenure Status - Whether judge has tenure
Reappointment Date - Date judge’s term expires for untenured judges. For judges with tenure, the date is the reappointment date.
Law School - Primary law school attended by judge. Field does not include other advanced degrees.
Start Date - Date judge took initial oath
Court - Name of court and date assigned
Division - Judge’s division assignment (Civil, Criminal, Family, General Equity, Assignment Judge, or Appellate Division)
Division Date - Date the judge changed divisions. If a judge is reassigned to a different county within the vicinage but does not change
divisions, the date is unchanged. If a judge is reassigned to a different county not within the vicinage but does not change divisions, a
note is listed at the bottom of the page with the date of the county change.
Appellate - If the judge is assigned to the Appellate Division, which part (section) and date the judge is assigned to the part. Summer parts
are not listed.
Presiding Judge - Whether the judge is a presiding judge, and the date the judge was assigned to preside over a division or in the Appellate
Division
Temporary Assignment - If the judge is temporarily assigned to a different court, the date of that temporary assignment and the court,
county, and division to which temporarily assigned
